      "markdown": "![img-7.jpeg](img-7.jpeg)\n\nFigure 5. Nanostructural analysis of astrocytic mitochondria, endoplasmic reticulum (ER), and mitochondria-ER contact sites (MERCs) (A) Reconstructed astrocytic mitochondria from two reference volumes in endfeet (left) and non-endfoot compartments (right).\n(B-D) Surface-to-volume ratio, mean total curvature, and mean local thickness of mitochondria.\n(E and F) SEM of endfoot mitochondria and MERCs. (Fi and Fii) MERCs are particularly prominent on the adluminal aspect of mitochondria.\n(G) Mitochondria in non-endfoot region.\n(H) Two separate reconstructions of endfoot ER. (Hi) Examples of ER passing through mitochondria. (Hii) Examples of ER cistern giving rise to an ER bridge though mitochondria. (Hiii) Two ER bridges traced with dotted line.\n(I) Endfoot (blue) and non-endfoot (magenta) mitochondria and MERCs (green)."
