 interval, only $\\sim 2.5 \\%$ of vertices in our datasets are lost at this resolution, suggesting viability of existing large datasets for relatively accurate ultrastructural studies of astrocytes. ${ }^{22,73}$ Advanced FIB-SEM machines ${ }^{74,75}$ combined with volume stitching ${ }^{76}$ may also be appropriate.\n\nFixation methodology must also be considered. Glutaraldehyde fixation causes tissue shrinkage; eliminates extracellular space; and alters cellular anatomy, particularly that of astrocytes. ${ }^{77}$ Cryofixation is a method used to preserve extracellular space. However, cryofixation requires dissection/slicing of fresh brain tissue. Brain ultrastructure in general, ${ }^{78}$ and astrocytes especially, ${ }^{79-82}$ are sensitive to slicing and mechanical stimulation. Astrocytes from acute slices show reduced spine coverage ( $32 \\%$ ) compared with astrocytes from perfusion-based fixation. ${ }^{33}$ Alternative chemical fixation approaches show promise"
